{
  "message": "feat: add GASTOWN_DISABLE_OFFER_ADD env var to suppress repo add prompt\n\nWhen GASTOWN_DISABLE_OFFER_ADD=1 is set, the shell integration skips\nthe \"Add '<repo>' to Gas Town?\" prompt entirely. Users who want Gas\nTown for specific workflows but never want the auto-add prompt can\nexport this in their shell profile.\n\nCloses GHI #1227.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>",
  "files": [
    {
      "sha": "86aa8474ed0a721903edcdc5463bbd45df577cee",
      "filename": "internal/shell/integration.go",
      "status": "modified",
      "additions": 2,
      "deletions": 1,
      "changes": 3,
      "blob_url": "https://github.com/gastownhall/gastown/blob/68ebad7e287150742ab7989b66f1a19b7fbddaa0/internal%2Fshell%2Fintegration.go",
      "raw_url": "https://github.com/gastownhall/gastown/raw/68ebad7e287150742ab7989b66f1a19b7fbddaa0/internal%2Fshell%2Fintegration.go",
      "contents_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/gastownhall/gastown/contents/internal%2Fshell%2Fintegration.go?ref=68ebad7e287150742ab7989b66f1a19b7fbddaa0",
      "patch": "@@ -187,7 +187,8 @@ _gastown_mark_asked() {\n \n _gastown_offer_add() {\n     local repo_root=\"$1\"\n-    \n+\n+    [[ \"${GASTOWN_DISABLE_OFFER_ADD:-}\" == \"1\" ]] && return 0\n     _gastown_already_asked \"$repo_root\" && return 0\n     \n     [[ -t 0 ]] || return 0"
    }
  ]
}
